member.summary: Last message ID, used to identify messages. Will increment for each message sent.

member.name: M:OSRSHelpers.GodlikeClient.SendMessage(System.String,System.Boolean)
member.summary:
Sends a message to the server.
Possible message types:
force #handler: Forces an update of data, specify #handler to only force update a specific handler.
Example: "force npc" will force an update of the NPC handler.
fetch #handler: Fetches data from specifed #handler, if is true, the method will wait and return the response when available, if false, the method will not wait and return null.
Example: "fetch npc" will fetch data of the NPC handler, and return the response if is true.
set #var #value: Sets a #var to the specified #value.
Example: "set close_npcs_max_distance 1500" will set the close_npcs_max_distance of the CloseNPCsHandler to 1500, which means it will only return npcs within 1500 units.
member.param: Whether to wait for a response or not. If true, the method will return the response, if false, the method will return null.
member.returns: Response from the server, if is true, otherwise null.

member.name: M:OSRSHelpers.GodlikeClient.ProcessContent(System.String)
member.summary: Process the content of a websocket message, and call subscribers.

member.name: M:OSRSHelpers.GodlikeClient.Subscribe(System.String,System.String,System.Action{System.String})
member.summary:
Subscribe to a data key. Subscribers will be cleared when the script is stopped.
When data is received, is called with the data as a string, if the data has changed.
Subscribing to a key will only retrieve data for that key, and not the entire container.
member.param: Action to call when data is received.

member.name: M:OSRSHelpers.GodlikeClient.Subscribe(System.String,System.Action{System.String})
member.summary:
Subscribe to a data container, without a key, which will retrieve all data in the container. Subscribers will be cleared when the script is stopped.
When data is received, is called with the data as a string, if the data has changed.
Subscribing to a container will retrieve all data in the container, and not just a single key.
member.param: Action to call when data is received.

member.name: M:OSRSHelpers.GodlikeClient.Unsubscribe(System.String,System.Action{System.String})
member.summary: Unsubscribe from a data container, without a key.
